For more information, please refer to Google's API Services User Data Policy(https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy) and Limited Use requirements(https://developers.google.com/terms).

#Information We Collect

Our Google Form Add-on uses a minimum amount of scopes, including two default scopes provided by Google and three additional scopes provided by Google Forms Script Editor.
These scopes allow us to access specific data and perform necessary actions within the add-on, such as creating and issuing certificates based on the responses provided by users in their Google Form submissions.

The scopes used in our Google Form Add-on include:

Google Sheets Scope: This scope allows us to read and write data to the Google Sheet that is associated with the Google Form. 
                     We use this scope to retrieve user responses and insert the certificate data into the sheet.
Google Drive Scope: This scope allows us to create and access files in the user's Google Drive account. 
                    We use this scope to create and store the certificate files that are generated by our add-on.
Google Forms Scope: This scope allows us to read and write data to the Google Form that is associated with the add-on. 
                    We use this scope to retrieve user responses and update the form status to indicate that the certificate has been issued.
                    
Our Google Form Add-on does not collect any personal information from users other than the information required for authentication and issuing certificates.
We only obtain information from users who have signed up for our services through our company configurations in the Google add-on after installation.
This information includes:

User Email Address: This is used to identify you as a user of our add-on and to authenticate you when you access the add-on.
User Password: This is used to authenticate you as a user of our add-on and to ensure that only authorized users can access the add-on.
User TemplateID: This is used to issue certificates through our add-on and to ensure that the correct certificate template is used for each user.

#How We Use Information

We use the information collected from our users solely for the purpose of issuing certificates through the Google Form Add-on.
We do not share this information with any third parties or use it for any other purposes.
We may use the email address provided by users to send occasional updates or promotional offers related to our services.
Users can opt-out of receiving these emails by contacting us at info@certifyme.cc.

#Data Security

We take appropriate measures to protect the personal information collected through our Google Form Add-on.
We use industry-standard encryption to ensure that all data is transmitted securely.
We also limit access to personal information to authorized personnel who have a legitimate need to access it.

#Changes to Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update or modify this privacy policy at any time.
If we make any significant changes, we will notify users by email or through our website.

